snippet.textDisplay:
They are produced in abundance since that’s what the industry believes are the colors people want. In fact it’s just because black, white, and silver are usually available on the cheapest base models. And people don’t want to pay extra for that special color option. I like cool colors but bought a silver car since it was $7k off sticker price.

I think most of us watching this agree market trends suck. Like you may like crossovers and SUVs but it’s not what we ALL want, yet that’s all that’s being produced. It’s forcing the lack of options.

Bring back sexy coupes and convertibles and big stately sedans. All with cool colors.
